# UCAB Cab Booking System – Project Execution Guide

## Overview
This document explains how to run the UCAB Cab Booking System on a local machine. The project is built using the MERN Stack (MongoDB, Express.js, React.js, Node.js).

---

## Prerequisites

Before running the application, make sure the following software is installed:

- Node.js (v16 or above)
- npm (v8 or above)
- MongoDB
- VS Code
- Git

---

# Step 1: Set Up the Frontend (React App)

Open a terminal and navigate to the client folder.

```bash
cd client

Install dependencies (if not already installed).

npm install

Start the React development server.

npm run dev

The frontend application will run at:

http://localhost:5173
Step 2: Set Up the Backend (Express Server)

Open a new terminal window.

Navigate to the server folder.

cd server

Install backend dependencies.

npm install
Step 3: Configure Environment Variables

Inside the server folder, create a file named:

.env

Add the MongoDB connection string:

MONGO_URI=mongodb://localhost:27017/UCAB
PORT=8000
JWT_SECRET=mysecretkey
Step 4: Start MongoDB

Ensure MongoDB service is running.

Verify MongoDB connection before starting the backend server.

Step 5: Start the Backend Server

Run the backend server using:

nodemon index.js

or

node index.js

Backend server will run at:

http://localhost:8000
Project Execution Flow
Start MongoDB
Start Backend Server
Start Frontend Server
Open Browser
Register/Login
Book Cab
View Booking History
Manage Data via Admin Panel
Expected Output

Frontend:
http://localhost:5173

Backend:
http://localhost:8000

Database:
MongoDB Local Server

Technologies Used
React.js
Node.js
Express.js
MongoDB
Axios
JWT Authentication
Bootstrap
Outcome

Successfully execute the UCAB Cab Booking System by running both frontend and backend servers and connecting them through MongoDB.


